parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering Rack and Pinion Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering rack and pinion can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.

The failure of the power steering hose can cause the loss of power steering fluid, leading to the loss of power steering assist, which can make it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the power steering pump can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Whining or grinding noise from the power steering pump

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive brake wear can cause the brakes to fail, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: grinding or screeching noise when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear on the suspension bushings can cause uneven tire wear, reduced handling, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Noise when going over bumps or uneven surfaces

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty brake system can cause the vehicle to fail to stop or slow down properly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes feel soft or spongy
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brakes fail to hold on uneven pavement
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected
the brakes produce a slipping or grabbing sensation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the vehicle to shut down, lose power, and experience various electrical issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down while driving
the check engine light is lit
the ignition system strains to turn over.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to lose power steering, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
The failure of the ignition and starting system can cause the vehicle to not start, which can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the ignition system strains to turn over

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to experience various electrical issues, which can lead to accidents or fires.
symptoms: A small flame appears from the power outlet
